ZCZC OE32
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
WEDNESDAY TO SATURDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 212300 UTC
ON WEDNESDAY EVENING LOW PRESSURE WILL BE MOV FM THE NORWEGIAN SEA AND
INTO SCANDINAVIA WHERE IT WILL CONTINUE TO FILL IN THE PROCESS. ANOTHER
AREA OF LOW PRESSURE WILL BE POSITIONED CLOSE TO SERN IBERIA DURING THE PERIOD.
MEANWHILE THE PORTPATRICK SEA AREAS WILL BE DOMINATED BY AN AREA OF HIGH
PRESSURE 1032 EXTENDING FM MAINLAND EUROPE ACROSS THE UK N SEA AND SERN
SCANDINAVIA. HIGH PRESSURE CENTRE WILL DRIFT SLWY WWARDS TO BECOME CENTRED
OVER THE NW OF THE UK BY THE END OF SATURDAY. LOW PRESSURE CENTRES WILL REMAIN
TO THE N W AND S OF THE ANTICYCLONE AND OUTSIDE OF UK SURROUNDING WATERS.
NO HAZARDOUS WINDS ARE EXP ACROSS PORTPATRICK THROUGHOUT THIS PERIOD BUT
COULD BE STRG FOR A TIME ACROSS S E ICELAND ON FRIDAY AND POSSIBLY INTO SATURDAY
ALTHOUGH WITH SOME UNCERTAINTY AT THIS STAGE
